basic.description:
An introduction to computer software consistent with modern professional practice of statistics. Use of the statistical package SAS and S-PLUS. Given jointly with STAT 862/3.0.
LEARNING HOURS    120 (36L;84P)
basic.subject: STAT
basic.title: Computational Data Analysis

extra.enrollment_requirement: Corequisite    STAT361 or ECON351 or permission of the Department.
